The paper focuses on enabling novice users to create effective task plans for collaborative robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The study also involves user experience and usability testing, which suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The CoSTAR system integrates perception and reasoning, which aligns with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the study involves varying perception capabilities, which suggests a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV).
